  # Why: Just-inside boundary — digest at exactly 700 tokens should be accepted
  # [ASSUMPTION: confidence=high] Maximum digest size is 700 tokens as stated in acceptance criteria
  @boundary
  Scenario: A digest of exactly 700 tokens is within the acceptable limit
    Given a role digest that is exactly 700 tokens
    When the digest is validated during prompt assembly
    Then the digest should be accepted without warning

  # Why: Just-outside boundary — digest exceeding 700 tokens should trigger a warning
  # [ASSUMPTION: confidence=high] Maximum digest size is 700 tokens as stated in acceptance criteria
  @boundary @negative
  Scenario: A digest exceeding 700 tokens triggers a validation warning
    Given a role digest that is 701 tokens
    When the digest is validated during prompt assembly
    Then a warning should indicate the digest exceeds the maximum size

  # Why: Boundary — zero input tokens should still produce a valid event
  @boundary
  Scenario: An LLM call with zero input tokens still emits a valid event
    Given an LLM call completes with zero input tokens
    When the "llm.call" event is emitted
    Then "input_tokens" should be 0
    And the event should still be structurally valid

  # Why: Boundary — first attempt vs subsequent attempts tracked correctly
  @boundary
  Scenario: The first attempt of a task is recorded as attempt 1
    Given a task starts for the first time
    When the "task.started" event is emitted
    Then the "attempt" field should be 1

  # Why: Boundary — wave with zero rate limit events should report zero
  @boundary
  Scenario: A wave with no rate limit events reports zero rate limit count
    Given a wave completes with no rate limit responses
    When the "wave.completed" event is emitted
    Then "rate_limit_count" should be 0
    And no concurrency adaptation should be triggered

  # Why: Just-inside boundary — rate limit count of 1 should trigger concurrency reduction
  # [ASSUMPTION: confidence=high] Any rate_limit_count > 0 triggers concurrency reduction per the adaptation policy
  @boundary
  Scenario: A wave with one rate limit event triggers concurrency reduction
    Given a wave completes with exactly 1 rate limit response
    When the "wave.completed" event is emitted
    Then "rate_limit_count" should be 1
    And concurrency should be reduced by 50%

  # Why: Boundary — p95 latency threshold for concurrency adaptation
  # [ASSUMPTION: confidence=medium] The configurable p95 threshold defaults to 2x baseline (100% increase)
  @boundary
  Scenario Outline: Concurrency adapts based on p95 latency change relative to threshold
    Given the p95 latency threshold for adaptation is <threshold_pct>% above baseline
    And the baseline p95 latency is <baseline_ms> ms
    When the current wave p95 latency is <current_ms> ms
    Then concurrency adaptation should <action>

    Examples:
      | threshold_pct | baseline_ms | current_ms | action                |
      | 100           | 5000        | 9999       | not be triggered      |
      | 100           | 5000        | 10001      | reduce concurrency    |

  # Why: Boundary — concurrency increase after stability period
  # [ASSUMPTION: confidence=medium] Stability window for concurrency increase is 5 minutes
  @boundary
  Scenario: Concurrency increases by 1 after the stability window elapses
    Given concurrency was previously reduced due to rate limiting
    And the system has been stable with no rate limits for 5 minutes
    When the next wave starts
    Then concurrency should increase by 1 worker

