  # Why: Invalid failure category should be rejected
  @negative
  Scenario: A task.failed event with an invalid failure category is rejected
    Given a task has failed
    When the event emitter attempts to emit a "task.failed" event with failure_category "unknown_reason"
    Then the event should be rejected
    And the error should indicate "unknown_reason" is not in the controlled vocabulary

  # Why: Invalid prompt profile should be rejected at configuration time
  @negative
  Scenario: Configuring an invalid prompt profile is rejected
    Given an operator sets the prompt profile to "full_rules_only"
    When the configuration is validated
    Then the configuration should be rejected
    And the error should list valid prompt profiles

  # Why: Missing required fields on llm.call should be caught
  @negative
  Scenario: An llm.call event missing required fields is rejected
    Given an LLM call completes
    When the event emitter attempts to emit an "llm.call" event without "latency_ms"
    Then the event should be rejected
    And the error should indicate the missing required field

  # Why: Secret redaction is mandatory for tool.exec events
  # [ASSUMPTION: confidence=medium] Standard redaction patterns: API keys, tokens, passwords in env vars
  @negative
  Scenario: A tool.exec event containing unredacted secrets is rejected
    Given the Player agent executes a command containing an API key in the arguments
    When the "tool.exec" event is assembled
    Then the "cmd" field should have the secret redacted
    And no secret values should appear in the emitted event

  # Why: A digest file that does not exist should fail gracefully
  @negative
  Scenario: A missing digest file for a role produces a clear error
    Given the Player digest file does not exist
    When the prompt assembler attempts to load the Player digest
    Then a clear error should indicate the digest file is missing
    And the system should not fall back to the full rules bundle silently

  # Why: Emitting an event with an invalid agent_role should be caught
  @negative
  Scenario: An event with an unrecognised agent role is rejected
    Given an event is being assembled with agent_role "supervisor"
    When the event emitter validates the event
    Then the event should be rejected
    And the error should indicate valid roles are player, coach, resolver, and router

