  # Why: Prefix cache hit detection on vLLM is approximate — the event must reflect this
  @edge-case
  Scenario: Prefix cache hit status from vLLM is reported as estimated when not directly provided
    Given the LLM provider is "local-vllm"
    And the vLLM response does not include a direct cache hit header
    When the "llm.call" event is assembled
    Then "prefix_cache_hit" should be present
    And it should be flagged as "estimated"

  # Why: Events must be emitted even when the LLM call itself fails
  @edge-case
  Scenario: A failed LLM call still emits an llm.call event with error details
    Given the Player agent makes an LLM call that times out
    When the "llm.call" event is emitted
    Then "status" should be "error"
    And "error_type" should be "timeout"
    And "latency_ms" should reflect the time spent before the timeout

  # Why: The migration path must not break existing behaviour during Phase 1
  @edge-case
  Scenario: Phase 1 migration preserves existing context behaviour while adding instrumentation
    Given the migration phase is Phase 1
    When an AutoBuild run executes
    Then the full rules bundle should still be injected alongside the role digest
    And the "prompt_profile" should be "digest+rules_bundle"
    And instrumentation events should be emitted for all LLM calls

  # Why: Graphiti unavailability should not break the pipeline
  @edge-case
  Scenario: Graphiti unavailability during a digest+graphiti run falls back gracefully
    Given the prompt profile is "digest+graphiti"
    And Graphiti is temporarily unavailable
    When the context loader attempts to retrieve context
    Then a "graphiti.query" event should be emitted with "status" as "error"
    And the run should continue with digest-only context
    And a warning should be logged about the Graphiti fallback

  # Why: Multiple waves must each produce independent wave events
  @edge-case
  Scenario: Each wave in a multi-wave run produces its own wave event
    Given an AutoBuild run with 3 waves
    When all 3 waves complete
    Then 3 separate "wave.completed" events should be emitted
    And each event should have a distinct "wave_id"
    And each event should include independent "queue_depth_start" and "queue_depth_end"

  # Why: Structured events must be written to local log when NATS is unavailable
  # [ASSUMPTION: confidence=high] Events are emitted as structured JSON over NATS and/or to local structured log file per spec
  @edge-case
  Scenario: Events are written to a local structured log file when NATS is unavailable
    Given the NATS event bus is not configured
    When an AutoBuild run completes and emits events
    Then all events should be written to the local structured log file
    And each event should be a valid JSON object on its own line

  # Why: A/B comparison requires identical task sets run under different profiles
  @edge-case
  Scenario: The same task produces comparable instrumentation data under different prompt profiles
    Given the same task definition is available
    When the task is run under "digest+rules_bundle" profile
    And the same task is run under "digest+graphiti" profile
    Then both runs should produce "task.completed" events with the same "task_id"
    And the instrumentation data should include "input_tokens" for both runs
    And the "latency_ms" values should be available for p50/p95 comparison

